This paper discusses the evaluation of text-to-text generation models, specifically in the context of Grammatical Error Correction (GEC) and Text Simplification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the biases in evaluation metrics, which could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the distribution of valid corrections, which could fall under the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
